Some unknown gunmen have reportedly kidnapped an officer of the Nigerian Navy in Kogi State. According to reports, the Naval officer identified as  Musa Lawal with enlistment no. X12775 ABRP3 was abducted on Monday night. The PUNCH reported that the officer serving with the Naval Headquarters in Abuja was whisked away from his residential home located behind Post Flood Housing Estate, in Lokoja at about 8:00 pm yesterday. The kidnappers reached out to the wife of the victim an hour after the kidnap, demanding three million naira as ransom. Narrating the unpleasant situation to newsmen, the wife of the kidnapped naval staff, Juliana Ida Musa said one of her husband’s hands was bleeding when he was being taken away. Meanwhile, the state Police Public Relations Officer, SP Williams Ayah is yet to confirm the incident